<div class="c290_16"> 
<div id="v290.16.1"><span class="H7971 s">Send</span><span class="H3733 s"> ye the lamb</span><span class="H4910 s"> to the ruler</span><span class="H776 s"> of the land</span><span class="H5554 s"> from Sela</span><span class="H4057 s"> to the wilderness</span><span class="H2022 s">, unto the mount</span><span class="H1323 s"> of the daughter</span><span class="H6726 s"> of Zion</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Sela: or, Petra: Heb. A rock)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.16.2"><span class="H5074 s">For it shall be, <i>that</i>, as a wandering</span><span class="H5775 s"> bird</span><span class="H7971 s"> cast out</span><span class="H7064 s"> of the nest</span><span class="H1323 s">, <i>so</i> the daughters</span><span class="H4124 s"> of Moab</span><span class="H4569 s"> shall be at the fords</span><span class="H769 s"> of Arnon</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (cast…: or, a nest forsaken)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.16.3"><span class="H935 s">Take</span><span class="H6098 s"> counsel</span><span class="H6213 s">, execute</span><span class="H6415 s"> judgment</span><span class="H7896 s">; make</span><span class="H6738 s"> thy shadow</span><span class="H3915 s"> as the night</span><span class="H8432 s"> in the midst</span><span class="H6672 s"> of the noonday</span><span class="H5641 s">; hide</span><span class="H5080 s"> the outcasts</span><span class="H1540 s">; bewray</span><span class="H5074 s"> not him that wandereth</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Take: Heb. Bring)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.16.4"><span class="H5080 s">Let mine outcasts</span><span class="H1481 s"> dwell</span><span class="H4124 s"> with thee, Moab</span><span class="H1933 s">; be</span><span class="H5643 s"> thou a covert</span><span class="H6440 s"> to them from the face</span><span class="H7703 s"> of the spoiler</span><span class="H4160 s">: for the extortioner</span><span class="H656 s"> is at an end</span><span class="H7701 s">, the spoiler</span><span class="H3615 s"> ceaseth</span><span class="H7429 s">, the oppressors</span><span class="H8552 s"> are consumed</span><span class="H776 s"> out of the land</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (extortioner: Heb. wringer) (the oppressors: Heb. the treaders down)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.16.5"><span class="H2617 s">And in mercy</span><span class="H3678 s"> shall the throne</span><span class="H3559 s"> be established</span><span class="H3427 s">: and he shall sit</span><span class="H571 s"> upon it in truth</span><span class="H168 s"> in the tabernacle</span><span class="H1732 s"> of David</span><span class="H8199 s">, judging</span><span class="H1875 s">, and seeking</span><span class="H4941 s"> judgment</span><span class="H4106 s">, and hasting</span><span class="H6664 s"> righteousness</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (established: or, prepared)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.16.6"><span class="H8085 s">We have heard</span><span class="H1347 s"> of the pride</span><span class="H4124 s"> of Moab</span><span class="H3966 s">; <i>he is</i> very</span><span class="H1341 s"> proud</span><span class="H1346 s">: <i>even</i> of his haughtiness</span><span class="H1347 s">, and his pride</span><span class="H5678 s">, and his wrath</span><span class="H907 s">: <i>but</i> his lies</span> <i>shall</i> not <i>be</i> so.</div> 
<div id="v290.16.7"><span class="H4124 s">Therefore shall Moab</span><span class="H3213 s"> howl</span><span class="H4124 s"> for Moab</span><span class="H3213 s">, every one shall howl</span><span class="H808 s">: for the foundations</span><span class="H7025 s"> of Kirhareseth</span><span class="H1897 s"> shall ye mourn</span><span class="H5218 s">; surely <i>they are</i> stricken</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (mourn: or, mutter)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.16.8"><span class="H7709 s">For the fields</span><span class="H2809 s"> of Heshbon</span><span class="H535 s"> languish</span><span class="H1612 s">, <i>and</i> the vine</span><span class="H7643 s"> of Sibmah</span><span class="H1167 s">: the lords</span><span class="H1471 s"> of the heathen</span><span class="H1986 s"> have broken down</span><span class="H8291 s"> the principal plants</span><span class="H5060 s"> thereof, they are come</span><span class="H3270 s"> <i>even</i> unto Jazer</span><span class="H8582 s">, they wandered</span><span class="H4057 s"> <i>through</i> the wilderness</span><span class="H7976 s">: her branches</span><span class="H5203 s"> are stretched out</span><span class="H5674 s">, they are gone over</span><span class="H3220 s"> the sea</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (stretched…: or, plucked up)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.16.9"><span class="H1058 s">Therefore I will bewail</span><span class="H1065 s"> with the weeping</span><span class="H3270 s"> of Jazer</span><span class="H1612 s"> the vine</span><span class="H7643 s"> of Sibmah</span><span class="H7301 s">: I will water</span><span class="H1832 s"> thee with my tears</span><span class="H2809 s">, O Heshbon</span><span class="H500 s">, and Elealeh</span><span class="H1959 s">: for the shouting</span><span class="H7019 s"> for thy summer fruits</span><span class="H7105 s"> and for thy harvest</span><span class="H5307 s"> is fallen</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the shouting…: or, the alarm is fallen upon, etc)</span></div> 
<div id="v290.16.10"><span class="H8057 s">And gladness</span><span class="H622 s"> is taken away</span><span class="H1524 s">, and joy</span><span class="H3759 s"> out of the plentiful field</span><span class="H3754 s">; and in the vineyards</span><span class="H7442 s"> there shall be no singing</span><span class="H7321 s">, neither shall there be shouting</span><span class="H1869 s">: the treaders</span><span class="H1869 s"> shall tread out</span><span class="H3196 s"> no wine</span><span class="H3342 s"> in <i>their</i> presses</span><span class="H1959 s">; I have made <i>their vintage</i> shouting</span><span class="H7673 s"> to cease</span>.</div> 
<div id="v290.16.11"><span class="H4578 s">Wherefore my bowels</span><span class="H1993 s"> shall sound</span><span class="H3658 s"> like an harp</span><span class="H4124 s"> for Moab</span><span class="H7130 s">, and mine inward parts</span><span class="H7025 s"> for Kirharesh</span>.</div> 
<div id="v290.16.12"><span class="H7200 s">And it shall come to pass, when it is seen</span><span class="H4124 s"> that Moab</span><span class="H3811 s"> is weary</span><span class="H1116 s"> on the high place</span><span class="H935 s">, that he shall come</span><span class="H4720 s"> to his sanctuary</span><span class="H6419 s"> to pray</span><span class="H3201 s">; but he shall not prevail</span>.</div> 
<div id="v290.16.13"><span class="H1697 s">This <i>is</i> the word</span><span class="H3068 s"> that the LORD</span><span class="H1696 s"> hath spoken</span><span class="H4124 s"> concerning Moab</span><span class="H227 s"> since that time</span>.</div> 
<div id="v290.16.14"><span class="H3068 s">But now the LORD</span><span class="H1696 s"> hath spoken</span><span class="H559 s">, saying</span><span class="H7969 s">, Within three</span><span class="H8141 s"> years</span><span class="H8141 s">, as the years</span><span class="H7916 s"> of an hireling</span><span class="H3519 s">, and the glory</span><span class="H4124 s"> of Moab</span><span class="H7034 s"> shall be contemned</span><span class="H7227 s">, with all that great</span><span class="H1995 s"> multitude</span><span class="H7605 s">; and the remnant</span><span class="H4592 s"> <i>shall be</i> very</span><span class="H4213 s"> small</span><span class="H3808 s"> <i>and</i> feeble</span><span class="H3524 s"> †</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (feeble: or, not many)</span></div></div> 
